            "id": "4576397",
            "title": "FTI Consulting to retain CEO Steve Gunby: FT",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>FTI Consulting<span> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FCN\" title=\"FTI Consulting, Inc.\">FCN</a></span>) </span>CEO<span> </span>Steve Gunby<span> </span>intends to stay at the helm of the consulting group until at least 2029 prompting the departure of his most likely successor, the <em>Financial Times</em> reported.</li>\n<li>Lars Faeste, who was hired from Boston Consulting Group in 2022, decided to leave FTI after it became clear a transition would be put off.</li>\n<li>Another potential leadership candidate, former chief growth officer<span> Carlyn Taylor had</span> left the company too, the report said.</li>\n<li>“Change in leadership is natural in professional services, and it enables us to continue to move forward as a firm as we refresh our leadership ranks with new talent,” an FTI spokesperson told FT.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder_news_bottom\"></div></body></html>",
